Service Catalog (Separate Domain)

This is one architectural decision I'd like to lock in early.

Products and services should not share the same lifecycle.

Instead, create a dedicated service domain:

Service Category
        │
        ▼
Service Type
        │
        ▼
Seller Service
        │
        ▼
Pricing
        │
        ▼
Availability
        │
        ▼
Bookings
        │
        ▼
Measurements
        │
        ▼
Service Orders

This separation avoids forcing booking, scheduling, measurements, and availability into the product model.

One Important Improvement

Instead of encoding gender into product types (e.g., "Men's Shirt" and "Women's Shirt"), model it as an attribute.

For example:

Category
    Clothing

Product Type
    Shirt

Target Audience
    Men

Later, the same Shirt product type can be used for:

Men
Women
Unisex
Boys
Girls

without duplicating product types.

